## Step 5: Update Render Environment Variables

### 5.1 Go to Render Dashboard
1. Go to your Render Web Service (or create new one)
2. Click on your service
3. Go to **"Environment"** tab

### 5.2 Add Environment Variables

Click **"Add Environment Variable"** and add:
```
DATABASE_CLIENT = postgres
DATABASE_URL = postgresql://user:password@host:5432/database

# OR individual fields:
DATABASE_HOST = dpg-xxxxx-xxx.render.com
DATABASE_PORT = 5432
DATABASE_NAME = poppyshotels_xxxx
DATABASE_USERNAME = poppyshotels_xxxx_user
DATABASE_PASSWORD = xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
DATABASE_SSL = true

# Other required variables
NODE_ENV = production
APP_KEYS = your-app-keys
API_TOKEN_SALT = your-salt
ADMIN_JWT_SECRET = your-secret
TRANSFER_TOKEN_SALT = your-salt
JWT_SECRET = your-secret